gomodel:SYNGO_5042  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: Northern blots for tissue from rats showed that Hypocretin accumulates postnatally specifically in the brain.\n\nFigure 3: Electron micrograph of immunoreactive bouton synapsing on dendritic shaft in the periaqueductal gray of the thalamus. Arrowheads indicate the electron-dense peroxidase staining of large, dense-core vesicles.\n\nThe hypocretin (Hcrt) protein was targeted by a polyclonal antiserum (matching Hcrt1 and Hcrt2 isoforms) against a chemically synthesized peptide corresponding to the C-terminal 17 amino acids of the rat preprohcrt sequence (hypothalamus-specific mRNA that encodes preprohypocretin, the precursor of hypocretin).. Experimental description: M&M: \"Immunohistochemistry. Adult male Wistar rats were deeply anesthetized with Nembutal and perfused transcardially with 0.9% saline followed by 4% paraformaldehyde and 0.25% glutaraldehyde in 0.1 M phosphate buffer. The brains were postfixed ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5042" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

